		<!-- message -->
		<div id="post_message_393036">Is this still up for discussion? I know I instigated the change, and I am not ungrateful that it was changed. I just really wish we could have slightly bigger Avatar dimensions, Size is more then fine. For example my Avatar I am displaying right now original size is 150w x 200h, and if you look at the space the forum generates by default, it is more then small enough to fit in there without causing a bit of problem for the forum. Also it is a scant 12.5kb, well under the 20kb limit. Of course right now the forum auto scales it down and it looks horrible, I cannot likewise scale it to the dimensions without it looking terrible in Photoshop. This is an EQ Pixel Army Avatar, which I know there are a ton of supporters here. The new on I created for myself I was using as a sig, but I just cannot stand using an avatar as a sig, however at the same time the dimensions here just make it look horrid despite me ensuring it meets the file size requirements.<br />
<br />
I am not asking for any further size in crease on the Signature, it is perfect and the file size is fine. File size on avatar is great as well, its just a dimensional requirement I am beefing at, I would think this  place of all places would at the minimum allow the size required by EQ Pixel army. Can we please have this small concession? 150w x 200h, maintaining the 20kb max file size.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
