    <td width="30" align="center" valign="middle"><img src="/forums/images/openq.gif" width="30" height="30" ></td>
    <td>
		<div align="left" style="font-size: 12px; color: #999999; font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">It matters because I, and others, find animation in a sig area annoying. Aesthetically I don't like threads that contain post after post with large animated graphical signatures.<br />
<br />
Allowing an animated avatar was a concession to those who want to animate, but at least avatar's are off to the side of a post and smaller in size.</div>
		</td>
